The [Password policies|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/password-policies-938859739.html] documentation states:
{quote}
If anyone has chosen the Keep me logged in option on the site login screen, they'll be forced to update their password after their login period expires (every 30 days).
{quote}
"Keep me logged in" is no longer an option in Cloud.  The documentation should be updated.

h3. Issue Summary
Org admins can't remove the 2FA for managed accounts when the user provisioning integration is on. The following message is displayed on the user's profile at the Org:
{quote}
*Two-step verification*
Go to your identity provider settings to manage how users log in with a second step.
{quote}

h3. Environment
An [Organization|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/organization-administration-938859734.html] with [user provisioning|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/user-provisioning-959305316.html] only and not [SAML|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/saml-single-sign-on-943953302.html].

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # A regular user enables Atlassian 2FA on their account
 # The org admin enables user provisioning, including the user above
# The user (now managed entirely by the IDP) loses their phone

h3. Expected Results
The org admin should be able to disable 2FA for that user, since it's still enabled in Atlassian

h3. Actual Results
Because the user is completely managed by the IDP, the message 
{quote}
Go to your identity provider settings to manage how users log in with a second step
{quote}
is shown instead. However, 2FA is enabled in Atlassian, and not in the IDP


h3. Workaround

The org admin can manipulate admin.atlassian.com, calling the endpoint using the browser's developer console:

{code}
fetch('https://admin.atlassian.com/gateway/api/adminhub/organization/<org-id>/members/<AAid of the affected user>/mfa', 
	{ 
		method: 'DELETE', 
		credentials: 'same-origin', 
		headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json' }  
	}
).then(console.log)
{code}
